I settled into a food-first strategy. Once I had an estimation of the speed of the predators, I realised that I could estimate roughly how many times I could feed before a predator near the edge of the screen might reach me, and began to prioritise gathering algae. I would feed a certain amount of times and then hide when it felt as if the predator was about to reach me. I didn't count specifically but I think it was about 4-5 times for the shark, 6-7 times for the squid, and 8-9 times for the jellyfish before I had to hide. I got a bit bold in later rounds and lost a few lives. I began to avoid checking in rounds where the water was cloudier because I found it more efficient to hide and reveal a small amount of water at the centre than to check one segment at a time of three or four.
